.TH BWW 1 "2026-03-20" "bwrapwrap 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bww \- run a command inside a bubblewrap sandbox
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bww
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bww
wraps bubblewrap (bwrap) to sandbox commands with sensible defaults.
Network is blocked, the filesystem is read-only except the current
directory, and namespaces are unshared.
.PP
PATH directories and common toolchains (cargo/rustup) are auto-detected
and bound read-only.
.PP
When the command name contains "claude", only the project session
directory for the current working directory
(\fI~/.claude/projects/<encoded-cwd>/\fR) is bound read-write.
Shared config files (\fI.credentials.json\fR, \fIsettings.json\fR,
\fICLAUDE.md\fR) are bound read-only. Other projects' session data
is never exposed. Use \fB--fork\fR to branch into an isolated
copy-on-write overlay instead.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-net
Allow network access (blocked by default).
.TP
.B \-\-ptrace
Allow ptrace (e.g., for strace or gdb).
.TP
.B \-\-fork\fR [\fINAME\fR]
Fork \fI~/.claude\fR via fuse-overlayfs so writes go to
\fI~/.bww/NAME/\fR without touching the real data.
Auto-names if NAME is omitted.
Prints a resume command on exit.
.TP
.B \-\-fork\-cleanup
Delete the fork directory on exit (ephemeral).
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Print the generated bwrap command instead of running it.
.TP
.B \-\-help\fR, \fB\-h
Show help and exit.
.SH MOUNTS
.TS
l l.
Mount	Mode
_
/usr, /lib, /lib64, /bin, /sbin	read-only
/etc/alternatives, /etc/fonts, /etc/ssl	read-only
/proc, /dev	standard
/tmp	tmpfs
Current working directory	read-write
~/.cargo, ~/.rustup (if present)	read-only
PATH directories	read-only
~/.claude/projects/<cwd-session>/	read-write (claude only)
~/.claude/{.credentials.json,settings.json,CLAUDE.md}	read-only (claude only)
.TE
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
# Run a script with no network
bww python3 script.py

# Allow network
bww \-\-net curl https://example.com

# Claude with real ~/.claude
bww \-\-net claude

# Forked ~/.claude (copy-on-write)
bww \-\-fork \-\-net claude

# Named fork, resumable later
bww \-\-fork=experiment \-\-net claude

# Inspect generated bwrap command
bww \-\-dry\-run echo hello
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.bww/
Fork overlay directories.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.B bubblewrap
(bwrap) is required. Install with:
.B sudo apt install bubblewrap
.PP
.B fuse-overlayfs
is required for \fB--fork\fR mode. Install with:
.B sudo apt install fuse-overlayfs
